  <brief_title>PPI Sequencing Study</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Study to Assess the Effectiveness of Esomeprazole 40 mg Once Daily in Subjects With Continuing Gastroesophageal Reflux Disease (GORD) Symptoms Following Treatment Wit a Previous Full Dose Proton Pump Inhibitor (PPI)</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>AstraZeneca</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>AstraZeneca</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess how patients with gastro-oesophageal reflux disease
      (heartburn) who are currently receiving treatment with a proton pump inhibitor but are still
      experiencing symptoms will benefit from a change in treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
